This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image datasets and generating false positives. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a supervised generative framework. The paper also discusses adversarial attacks, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of generative models suggests it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
